<subSubSection pageId="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[707,1194,1442,1729]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,836,1496,1517]" pageId="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[966,1103,1495,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maracayensis">
<emphasis box="[966,1103,1495,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7">maracayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup, only in specimens of this species are the elytra mostly yellow and the elytral apex black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" pageId="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[707,1194,1442,1729]" lastBlockId="9.[173,659,194,614]" lastPageId="9" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,906,1576,1597]" pageId="7">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 8.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,762,1602,1623]" pageId="7">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation box="[834,904,1602,1623]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="21.[197,237,1489,1508]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,194,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-75@21.[172,1193,192,1465]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs. 92–97. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 92) P. helvinus; 93) P. maracayensis; 94) P. modestus; 95) P. bilineatus;" pageId="7">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[915,1028,1602,1623]" pageId="7">Integument</emphasis>
: Cranium mostly black, lower frons and venter yellow; pronotum reddish yellow, infuscated at base; elytra mostly yellow, infuscated at base and in apical region; femora decreasingly infuscated from profemur to metafemur; tibiae increasingly more yellow from protibia to metatibia; pterothorax and abdomen brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[255,311,247,268]" pageId="9">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes as wide as frons (14:14); funicular antennomeres conspicuously expanded, 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[184,197,295,309]" fontSize="6" pageId="9">th</superScript>
antennomere large (
<figureCitation box="[392,463,300,321]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[175,216,1487,1506]" captionTargetBox="[167,1170,207,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[151,1172,183,1487]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 21–38. Pujoliclerus species, antennae. 21) P. helvinus; 22) P. maracayensis; 23) P. bilineatus; 24) P. calceatus; 25) P. corumba; 26) P. ovatus; 27) P. wappesi; 28) P. amplus; 29) P. flavoapicalus; 30) P. gilvus; 31) P. hermani; 32) P. alajuela; 33) P. orellana; 34) P. megacavus; 35) P. oxinus; 36) P. alboordinus; 37) P. apolegmus; 38) P. catarina." pageId="9">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[481,554,300,321]" pageId="9">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum transverse (39:35), lateral tubercle very prominent (
<figureCitation box="[180,257,354,375]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="9">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
); epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[300,397,407,428]" pageId="9">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available.
</paragraph>
